  "texts": [
    "Codon usage refers to the frequency with which different codons are used to encode amino acids in a genome.",
    "When a virus's codon usage matches that of its host, it suggests that the virus has evolved to efficiently exploit the host's translational machinery, enhancing its ability to replicate within that host.",
    "This provides critical information in predicting potential virus-host interactions.",
    "By performing joint analysis of codon usage and other genomic features, researchers can achieve more accurate predictions regarding which host species are susceptible to particular viruses.",
    "Since these genomic features are embedded in the viral or bacterial genomes, it is possible to learn these features automatically using machine learning and AI methods."
  ],
